answers.text: Instagram is a photo and video-sharing social networking service owned by Facebook, Inc. It was created by Kevin Systrom and Mike Krieger, and launched in October 2010 exclusively on iOS.

Instagram is a platform where users can share images and videos, follow other users and interact with their content. It also offers features like Stories, IGTV for longer videos, and Shopping for businesses.
Instagram is a popular social media app that allows for photo and video sharing, live streaming, and exploring content from a global community of creators.
